# Academic Plagiarism Intelligence System

## Overview
This project is an advanced Python-based plagiarism detection and text analysis system designed to analyze large academic datasets using multiple pattern searching algorithms.

The system simulates 500 student submissions and detects copied content, repeated technical definitions, and document similarity using intelligent pattern matching techniques.

---

## Algorithms Implemented
- KMP (Knuth-Morris-Pratt)
- Rabin-Karp
- Boyer-Moore
- Naive Pattern Matching

---

## Features
- Simulates 500 academic documents
- Detects copied paragraphs and repeated patterns
- Calculates document similarity percentage
- Finds matched text positions
- Generates plagiarism risk levels
- Benchmarks algorithm performance
- Produces graphical analytical reports
- Displays top repeated patterns
- Generates similarity heatmaps

---

## Technologies Used
- Python 3.x
- Matplotlib
- NumPy
- Rich Library

---

## Python Libraries Used

| Library | Purpose |
|---|---|
| random | Generate synthetic documents |
| time | Measure execution time |
| hashlib | Fingerprint generation |
| difflib | Similarity comparison |
| itertools | Pairwise combinations |
| collections | Frequency counting |
| dataclasses | Structured result storage |
| typing | Type hints |
| numpy | Numerical operations |
| matplotlib | Graphical visualization |
| rich | Advanced terminal UI |

